{"id":"07-dictionaries","level":4,"title":"Dictionaries","category":"python","categoryLabel":"Python","points":250,"description":"Fix dict syntax.","objectives":["Quote keys","Use brackets to access"],"hints":["{'key': 'value'}"],"hintPenalty":30,"validationType":"python-output","files":[{"filename":"dicts.py","language":"python","editable":true,"content":"person = {\n    name: \"Alice\",\n    age: 25\n}\nprint(person.name)\nfor key, value in person:\n    print(f\"{key}: {value}\")"}],"validation":{"checks":[{"description":"quoted keys","astRule":{"type":"contains-string","value":"\"name\":"},"points":30},{"description":"brackets","astRule":{"type":"contains-string","value":"person[\"name\"]"},"points":35},{"description":".items()","astRule":{"type":"contains-string","value":"person.items()"},"points":35}]},"unlockRequires":["06-inheritance"]}
